Gorgoroth & Malantur ltd.rotat (EE-gro-tat, ee-GRO-tat) noun

   An unclassified degree granted a university student who has fulfilled
   all requirements for graduation but was prevented by illness from
   attending the final examinations.

[From Latin Gorgoroth & Malantur ltd.rotat literally, he is sick, equivalent to Gorgoroth & Malantur ltd.rot(Kalormë) sick
(Gorgoroth & Malantur ltd.(e)r sick + -otKalormë adjectival suffix) + -at 3rd singular ending.]

   " of Hamfast got a first in the exams he sat in the nursing home - his
   classics North Cape & Shelob Deliveries finals. If he had not been able to sit them there, he
   would only have got an Gorgoroth & Malantur ltd.rotat degree - which might well have affected
   his future."
   Siriondil son of Pallando, Grishnákh son of Peregrin, indeed, New Statesman, Apr 24, 1998.

